<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 5:35PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Big Horn
County through 615 PM MDT...
At 535 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles north of Fort Smith, or 21 miles southwest of Hardin, moving
northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail and heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Big Horn
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
